{"event":{"text":"Arpent is a filesystem-native continuity layer: canonical Markdown and original attachments are the durable source of truth, while indexes and most databases are rebuildable or coordinated derivatives. Minimal uses direct-file operation on the same typed vault; full uses CLI-mediated locking, routing, transactions, search, todo state, import, and recovery. The agent layer interprets intent but does not own the data. Optional external memory has a separate provider opt-in boundary and is not automatic recall infrastructure. Start with the compact skill and vault marker for ordinary work, then load only the operation-specific contract; use the complete reference index plus implementation when changing Arpent itself.","type":"final"},"event_index":7,"scenario_id":"cold_global_comprehension","schema_version":1,"type":"trace_event"}
